The Kilifi county government intends to grow its mining sector to diversify economic activities, Governor Amason Kingi (pictured) has said. He said his administration will work closely with the Mining ministry.Kingi spoke when Mining Cabinet Secreatry Dan Kazungu and ministry officials visited the Coast. He addressed the press at his office ahead of the Kilifi County International Investment Conference on Friday. Kingi said Kilifi has vast mineral deposits.